This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D medical image segmentation using a neural architecture search framework. It also involves optimizing the neural architecture using a stochastic sampling algorithm, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of gradient-based optimization and continuous relaxation techniques suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of medical images suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
